      "notes": "Sister to the well-known experimental HBC 472, Sabro exhibits many of the same characteristics, such as the coconut aroma. It imparts a strong and complex fruit flavour to beer, and has been described as having a mango, grapefruit, lemon grass and wood aroma, as well as the unique coconut.\nPEDIGREE\n“Unique cross pollenatoin with female neomexicanus ”\nRECOMMENDED BEER STYLES\nAmerican Pale Ale/Cream Ale, IPA, NEIPA, Porter, Stout\nKEY FLAVOURS\nTangerine, coconut, tropical and stone fruit with hints of cedar\nTOTAL OIL COMPOSITION\nAlpha w/w – 12.0-16.0%\nBeta w/w – 4-7%\nTotal Oils mls/100gm – 2.5-3.0\nCohumulone – 20-24% of alpha acids\nMyrcene (of total oil) – 55-65%\nCaryophyllene (of total oil) – 11-13%\nHumulene (of total oil) – 8-10%\nFarnesene (of total oil) – <1%",
